Detailed Code Implementation for 12-Pair Bridge System
Here's the full prototype code for the 12-pair system, merged with your G2 compact and descent chain. It implements:

12 pairs as mini-bridges (each (2,0), ds¬≤_i = dy_{1i}¬≤ + dy_{2i}¬≤).
Per-pair OR Reduction (localized sampling).
Residue splitting per pair (asymmetric for primes).
Pressure/breathing averaged across pairs.
Cyclic return per pair (multi-M√∂bius).

Run this ‚Äî it's self-contained, residue-tuned (adjust arrays for w=-0.958).
Pythonimport numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D
from scipy.integrate import odeint
import sympy as sp

# =====================================================
# 12-Pair Bridge System in (24,1) Dual-Shadow Descent
# Principia Metaphysica - v21.1 Extension Prototype
